OL,3,CShop prices fall for first time in
OL,4,Cnearly three years
OL,6,FMeanwhile, food prices were up 2% in
OL,7,FAugust, compared with the previous
OL,8,Fyear.
OL,10,FFresh food inflation slowed to 1% in
OL,11,FAugust ` with fruit, meat and fish
OL,12,Fseeing the biggest monthly decrease
OL,13,Fsince December 2020, the British
OL,14,FRetail Consortium (RBC) said.
OL,16,FAmbient food inflation ` which means
OL,17,Fproducts that can be safely stored at
OL,18,Froom temperature, such as tinned
OL,19,Fgoods, crisps, tea bags and biscuits `
OL,20,Fremained more stubborn at 3.4%.
